ChargeCtrl2.description: Register ChargeCtrl2, Address: h0b, Memory Index: 11

StepChgThs.description:
Step Charge voltage threshold in 4.6875mV steps.
VBATSTPCHG=((value+1)*4.6875mV)+3.6V. Writing a value greater than 0xDF (4.65V) will be held at 4.65V.
Writing a value greater than 0xDF (4.65V) will be held at 4.65V and the value of the register will be clamped to this max allowed value. 
Writing a value greater thanVBatReg won't be allowed and the actual value will be clamped to VBatReg.

ChargeCtrl3.description: Register ChargeCtrl3, Address: h0c, Memory Index: 12

VBatReg.description:
Battery regulation voltage in CV mode in 4.6875mV steps.
VBATREG=((value+1)*4.6875mV)+3.6V. 
Writing a value greater than 0xDF (4.65V) will be held at 4.65V and the value of the register will be clamped to this max allowed value. 
Writing a value less than StepChgThs won't be allowed and the actual value will be clamped to StepChgThs.

Buck1Mode.description:
Buck1 Operating Mode.

0b01: Force DCM. Current limited to TBD max (might need value based on programmed Ton), use for optimum ripple at low load current.
0b10: Force DCM low power. Current limited to TBD max (might need value based on programmed Ton), use for maximum efficiency at low load currents.

ThmADCV.description:
Output value from Thermistor ADC. Value is a percentage of pullup voltage at BTPU pin. 256 values in 0.39% steps. 
- ADC is active if CHGIN is valid (see Table 1) and ThmEn=1 or CHGIN not valid and ThmADCEn=1. 
- If ThmADCFltr=1, ThmADCEn=1 and CHGIN not valid, ThmADCEn will be the new value after ThmADC interrupt. 
- If ThmADCFltr=0, ThmADCEn=1 and CHGIN not valid, ThmADCEn will be updated with a new value every ADC conversion (approx. TBDµs) and ThmADC interrupt will not be generated

trigger_command.description: Triggers the start of selected command. This bit reset when the command execution has completed.

command.description:
Selection of the command to be executed on NVM:
000: read region (defined by start address and byte #, if margin read bit are set content of register file is compared NVM)
001: Read User region
010: Read Trim region
011: Program region
100: Read status bits

command_diag.description:
Outcome from last command execution
000: Command executed OK
001: Failure in margin read pre-program (tried to program 0 a bit already programmed to 1)
010: Failure in margin read post-program
011: Trim region not valid
other: reserved

read_opt.description:
1) RD[1:0]=00 : Normal read mode
2) RD[1:0]=01 : ‘1’(programmed) read margin check (Decrease high data sensing margin)
3) RD[1:0]=10 : ‘0’(initial) read margin check (Decrease low data sensing margin)
4) RD[1:0]=11 : N/A
